00:18:43,416 --> 00:18:45,208
Here's an idea,
attack number...

426
00:18:45,291 --> 00:18:46,875
--[dog barks]
--did you cry or did you laugh?

427
00:18:46,958 --> 00:18:48,375
--I laughed.
--I cried.

428
00:18:48,458 --> 00:18:49,958
Okay, what's your
favorite manga?

429
00:18:50,041 --> 00:18:52,875
[BOTH]
"Keroro Gunso."

430
00:18:52,958 --> 00:18:54,666
[sighs] I can't
really tell if these

431
00:18:54,750 --> 00:18:56,666
guys are the same
or not anymore.

432
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:59,791
Why don't you join the manga
club or something, Kona-chan?

433
00:18:59,875 --> 00:19:01,666
I mean, you like manga.

434
00:19:01,750 --> 00:19:04,000
Yeah, I guess I wouldn't mind
joining up with those guys,

435
00:19:04,083 --> 00:19:06,750
I'm pretty sure they've
at least got flexible hours.

436
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:08,500
Draw draw draw draw.

437
00:19:08,583 --> 00:19:10,750
[gasps] What the,
you call this drawing?

438
00:19:10,833 --> 00:19:12,791
Mm-hmm.

439
00:19:12,875 --> 00:19:15,541
I got a question, this thing
here, who's it a picture of?

440
00:19:15,625 --> 00:19:16,833
[KONATA]
That's Tsukasa.

441
00:19:16,916 --> 00:19:18,500
[TSUKASA]
Really? That's me?

442
00:19:18,583 --> 00:19:20,125
[KONATA]
And that's Miyuki-san.

443
00:19:20,208 --> 00:19:22,083
[KAGAMI] I guess you
sorta got the feel for her.

444
00:19:22,166 --> 00:19:23,791
[KONATA] This is Kagami.

445
00:19:23,875 --> 00:19:26,333
[KAGAMI]
Oh, I breathe fire, huh?

446
00:19:26,416 --> 00:19:29,500
My, it's the spitting
image of you isn't it?

447
00:19:29,583 --> 00:19:32,041
What a scary little girl,
how frightening.

448
00:19:32,125 --> 00:19:34,416
Would you cut it out already?!

449
00:19:34,500 --> 00:19:37,125
Oh, the new "Fullmetal"
book just came out.

450
00:19:37,208 --> 00:19:40,041
Yeah, the new issue of
"Compti" came out today too.

451
00:19:40,125 --> 00:19:42,750
I'm gonna swing by Gamers
now, do you guys wanna go?

452
00:19:42,833 --> 00:19:45,625
Oh, sorry, I think I'll just
go by the local bookstore today

453
00:19:45,708 --> 00:19:47,416
I got errands to run.

454
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:49,583
But you have to come with
me to Gamers today 'cause

455
00:19:49,666 --> 00:19:51,458
it'll nurture
the friendship between us.

456
00:19:51,541 --> 00:19:55,166
Stop it. What's up with you
today? You use a word like

457
00:19:55,250 --> 00:19:57,125
friendship and it doesn't
fit you at all.

458
00:19:57,208 --> 00:19:59,416
Oh, yeah, that, I was
just trying to get you to

459
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:00,875
give me all your
purchase points

460
00:20:00,958 --> 00:20:02,750
by appealing to your sense
of loyalty.

461
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:04,958
So that's all
my friendship means to you?

462
00:20:05,041 --> 00:20:06,541
What a crock.

463
00:20:06,625 --> 00:20:08,958
[GROUP]
Lucky Star!

464
00:20:14,250 --> 00:20:16,625
Man, it's quiet,
is she mad I used

465
00:20:16,708 --> 00:20:20,833
the sunflowers
